<br>
Once in shadow haven, a 16 necro that was soloing phlargs got diseased and was sitting around the mini-nexus waiting for a cure. No one was on and when I told him to use BW, he laughed and said it was a useless skill. Then he died. He just sat there and died. /boggle<br>
<br>
Another time in nertherbian lair (I like to hand around the nexus <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), a soloing SK was /oocing for heals. I told him to get some bandages and the 3 or 4 other people in the zone commented on how much it sucked.<br>
<br>
Just yesterday I was in a group at mons letalis (got bored soloing) and some iksar warrior 1 level higher than me kept asking my group's cleric and shamans for heals! I was below him in level and soloing the mobs solo with BW. <br>
<br>
Why is it that no one puts this skill to use? Sure, at level 10 it's expecive but after that it's pretty easy to maintain. With indiff faction and 115 cha I can get an 8 slot bag full of bandages for some 12pp. At 27, I get about 33hp per bandage. Hmm, 34 HP per tick. Sounds good to me. Why is it that no one else bothers? Is this skill just a waste at high levels? I'd imagine with the 3 different bind wound AAs we wars get, it would at least be put to use.<br>
<br>
Also, does anyone have any numbers on mith's binding and bandage wound? I'd imagine with those maxxed and a high BW skill, a war would be able to AAXP solo quite well. Or has PoP destroyed solo exping for all but the most solo-based classes? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thehawnz>the hawnz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.fotki.com/v13/photos/4/41603/158712/noble-vi.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 4:56:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2581.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Am I the only one?</span><hr size=1> warrior soloing will never reap very good exp at high levels.  and most warriors consider the bind wound aa's a waste of points since there's so many other aa skills that we practically NEED just to be able to tank stuff reliably. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kailynofpovar>Kailyn Of Povar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 5:53:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2581.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left c